Screenreader support.

Screenreader support changes some command output so it is easier to hear through
a screenreader.

Common forms:

set screenreader on
  Turn screenreader support on.

set screenreader off
  Turn screenreader support off.

set
  Show your current settings.

When screenreader support is on, some commands use plainer language, fewer
visual tables, and less decorative formatting. The help command also checks
/public/docs/vihelp first for screenreader-specific help topics, then falls back to the
normal help system.

Useful screenreader-friendly commands include look, actions, exits, npcs,
players, items, inventory, score, and who.
